text: Phiala alba is a moth in the family Eupterotidae. It was described by Per Olof Christopher Aurivillius in 1893. Note: This source has 1895 as the year of description. It is found in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (Katanga), Eritrea, Ethiopia, Malawi and Tanzania. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1893 Category:Eupterotinae
title: Phiala alba
